<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-36-1233 </DOCNO><TEXT>The interaction of the {alpha} particles produced in the fusion reactionwith high-frequency, one-dimensional magnetic acoustic solitons and low-frequency,two-dimensional drift vortices is analyzed in the approximation of astraight and uniform magnetic field. This interaction is shown to amplifythese plasma structures. This amplification may result in an additionaldiffusion of particles of the fusion plasma and a heat loss.</TEXT></DOC>